BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes,Lectures
DESCRIPTION:Join EHS Chemical Safety and Biological Safety for Laboratory S
 afety Week Feb. 9 through Feb. 13. This is an annual event dedicated to rec
 ognizing the successes of laboratory health and safety programs while provi
 ding valuable resources to keep our faculty\, staff and students safe.\n\n 
 \n\nAll week long\, EHS will be hosting a series of fun\, interactive train
 ings and workshops. Sign up for workshops that interest you and learn somet
 hing new!\n\n \n\nMaking Safety a Habit: Laboratory Safety Supervisor Works
 hop\n\nThis interactive workshop will help you learn all about safety super
 visor roles and requirements including how to make safety a habit and bring
 ing some fun safety activities back to the lab for a better safety culture.
 \n\n \n\nSharps Safety Workshop\n\nIf you work with needles\, razor blades\
 , or any sharps\, this will be the workshop for you! Partnered with Fisher 
 Scientific. Donuts and coffee will be available.\n\n \n\nAnimal Handling an
 d Occupational Safety\n\nThis great workshop will cover animal handling pre
 sented by Sherie Quillen\, Training Specialist from the Division of Compara
 tive Medicine and the University Employee Occupational Health Clinic.\n\n \
 n\nMental Wellness in the Lab presented by SWELL and a Chemical Compatibili
 ty Workshop\n\nLearn about psychological safety and the importance of welln
 ess and then join us for an interactive session about chemical compatibilit
 y from the Chemical Safety Team.\n\n \n\nIn addition\, we’ll be holding a d
 aily prize giveaway! Starting Feb. 10\, visit go.unc.edu/labsafetyweek26 ea
 ch day for a safety question. Submit your answer for a chance to win. The c
 orrect (or closest) answer will win the prize pin* of the day!\n\n \n\n*Pri
 ze pins are from dOrbital Games
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260209
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Lab Safety Awareness Week
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52002236899414
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/lab-safety-awareness-week
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Exhibits,Lectures,Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:Exploring the Foundations of Artificial Intelligence\n\nEvery A
 I breakthrough starts with a fundamental question: How do machines actually
  learn? On February 9th\, see how UNC Computer Science faculty are answerin
 g that question through groundbreaking research in neural architectures\, v
 ideo understanding\, language models\, and intelligent robotics. Join us fo
 r lightning talks\, live demonstrations\, and candid discussions about the 
 computational foundations that make artificial intelligence possible.\n\n \
 n\nAbout This Event\n\nWhile ChatGPT captures headlines\, our researchers a
 re inventing the next generation of algorithms that will define what’s poss
 ible five years from now. From revolutionary ego-exo learning that teaches 
 AI to see from multiple perspectives\, to self-correcting AI agents that ca
 tch their own mistakes\, discover the actual science behind machine intelli
 gence. You’ll leave understanding not just what AI can do\, but how and why
  it works—knowledge that transforms how you think about this technology con
 tributes to the broader AI ecosystem at Carolina and beyond. Note: This eve
 nt complements the university-wide AI Day in April. While that event explor
 es AI applications across all disciplines\, Core AI focuses specifically on
  the foundational computer science research that makes those applications p
 ossible.\n\n \n\nDate: February 9\, 2026\n\nVenue: Sitterson Hall (201 S. C
 olumbia Street)\n\nDuration: 8:30 AM – 3:00 PM\n\n \n\nSchedule\n\n8:30 AM 
 Registration & Breakfast\n\n9:30 AM Opening Ceremony/Remarks\n\n10:00 AM Co
 re UNC CS AI Faculty Lightning Talks\n\n12:20 PM Networking Lunch & AI Rese
 arch Fair (register to be part of the research fair here.)\n\n2:00 PM Panel
 : Core to Application: How AI Research Enables Discovery Across Carolina\n\
 n \n\nFull schedule details and registration information can be found here.
DTEND:20260209T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260209T133000Z
LOCATION:Sitterson Hall 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:CoreAI UNC CS Research Showcase
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51895494601420
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/coreai-unc-cs-research-showcase
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Implementing discipline over our emotional life is difficult an
 d requires lifelong practice. Being able to choose to act or respond in a p
 articular manner is preferable to re-acting on a consistent basis\, yet it 
 is difficult. Enhancing emotional intelligence improves our ability to mast
 er our emotional functioning. High emotional intelligence can improve our c
 ommunications with all others\, enhance our perception of satisfaction with
  ourselves and our lives and increase our productiveness overall.\n\n \n\nW
 orkshop Objectives\nAt the end of this workshop\, you will be able to:\nDes
 cribe the difference between intelligence and emotional intelligence\n• Des
 cribe the benefits of having emotional intelligence\n• Describe the compone
 nts of emotional intelligence\n• Identify the function and qualities of emo
 tions\n• Identify ways of assessing your emotional intelligence\nDescribe s
 trategies for improving emotional intelligence\n• Describe how to improve y
 our capacity for emotional self-control through mindfulness meditation\, mo
 nitoring\nself-statements and active listening\n• Describe how to accept re
 sponsibility for emotions and ways to teach emotional intelligence to child
 ren.\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link and select the “Req
 uest” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260209T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260209T150000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Emotional Intelligence
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51269488931894
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/emotional-intelligence
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This workshop covers the basic features of Lean Library Workspa
 ce (fka: Sciwheel)\, a tool available for free through UNC\, that can be us
 ed to organize and annotate references\, and create citations and bibliogra
 phies. It will focus on setting up your Lean Library Workspace account\, us
 ing Lean Library Workspace to organize and annotate references\, and genera
 ting citations and bibliographies in Word. It is structured for new to begi
 nning users.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences Li
 brary and led by Sydney Larson.
DTEND:20260209T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260209T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Lean Library Workspace (Sciwheel): Create Citations and Bibliograph
 ies
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764834476808
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/lean-library-workspace-sciwheel-create-c
 itations-and-bibliographies-6917
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Fears about job security have always had a negative impact on w
 orkplaces. Recent advancements in AI have accelerated and amplified those f
 ears. This session will explore how leaders can mitigate the negative effec
 ts of job insecurity on employee engagement and well-being.\n\nWorkshop Obj
 ectives:\n\n• Describe how fears about job security can impact employee wel
 l-being\n• Describe how fears about job security can impact employee engage
 ment\n• Take steps as a leader to counter the negative impacts of job insec
 urity on the workforce\n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link and se
 lect the “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260209T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260209T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Impacts of Job Insecurity on Employees Engagement and Well-bein
 g
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51561004127897
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/the-impacts-of-job-insecurity-on-employe
 es-engagement-and-well-being
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:AI in Research: Driving Innovation Forward\n\nDiscover how arti
 ficial intelligence can streamline workflows\, uncover hidden patterns\, an
 d empower breakthroughs in your field. Learn practical applications of AI t
 hrough Odum Institute AIR series that can revolutionize your research proce
 ss.\n\n \n\nThis course offers an overview of how AI tools such as large la
 nguage models (LLMS) can enhance early stages of the survey process\, inclu
 ding item generation\, questionnaire evaluation\, and survey refinement. Th
 is session will highlight practical ways LLMs such as ChatGPT and Microsoft
  Copilot can support researchers while also addressing common pitfalls. Par
 ticipants will learn best practices for questionnaire design focusing on wr
 iting questions\, response option development\, and question ordering. Idea
 l for researchers seeking to incorporate AI thoughtfully and efficiently du
 ring survey development work. The first half of the session will provide st
 ructured lecture content\, and the second half will offer time for particip
 ants to ask questions and discuss the specific projects they are working on
 .\n\nYou must have a UNC Chapel Hill Onyen to register and attend this cour
 se. No registration fees required but you must register to secure your spot
  and receive the Zoom link.
DTEND:20260209T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260209T180000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:AI in Research Series – Using AI in Survey Research: Practices and 
 Pitfalls
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51577968888784
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/ai-in-research-series-using-ai-in-survey
 -research-practices-and-pitfalls
END:VEVENT
