BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Mixed methods research (MMR) refers to research design and impl
 ementation that combines qualitative and quantitative data collection and/o
 r analysis strategies. This seminar explores strategies for effectively des
 igning\, implementing\, and integrating MMR. Through discussion of exemplar
 s and theoretical frameworks\, we will consider best practices for “mixing”
  methods and presenting integrated findings. Participants will gain practic
 al skills for aligning methodological choices with research questions\, imp
 lementing complementary qualitative and quantitative techniques\, and artic
 ulating cohesive and rigorous mixed methods results. Registration and fee (
 refundable for UNC students) are required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260210T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260210T140000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Integrated Mixed Methods
