DESCRIPTION:R is a free and open-source way to explore and analyze data\, i
 ncluding spatial data. In this workshop\, we will introduce you to spatial 
 analysis and visualization techniques in RStudio. We will use packages like
  sf\, tidycensus\, tigris\, terra\, and more to demonstrate typical GIS wor
 kflows and produce basic maps.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is designed for partic
 ipants with some familiarity with R/RStudio and/or GIS. If you need some ad
 ditional background\, feel free to join our beginR series or our ArcGIS Pro
  for Beginners workshop earlier in the semester. \n\n \n\nThis workshop is 
 offered by the University Libraries and will be led by librarians Philip Mc
 Daniel and Matthew Jansen. \n\n \n\nThis workshop is being offered remotely
  via Zoom only. Registrants will receive a Zoom link\; those on the waitlis
 t will not receive a Zoom link unless they are bumped up to a registered sp
 ot. After the workshop\, registrants and those on the waitlist will receive
