BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Academic Calendar,Lectures
DESCRIPTION:Kate Bowler will deliver the 2026 Frey Lecture. Bowler is a fou
 r-time New York Times bestselling author\, host of the award- winning Every
 thing Happens podcast and a professor of American religious history at Duke
  University. She is also as human as it gets. After several years of being 
 told her cancer was incurable\, she was declared cancer-free. But there's n
 o going back to what life was before for Bowler. Today\, she's on a mission
  to untangle our culture's obsession with toxic positivity and self-help an
 d permit you to be human. \n\nRegistration is required. Tickets are free\, 
 but registration is required. Learn more about Bowler on the Frey Lecture w
 ebsite.
DTEND:20260210T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
