CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This course is the second in a two-part scale development cours
 e series on scale development. Part one of the series focused on the genera
 l theories and methods used in the scale development process. This second p
 ortion focuses on the analytic methods used to statistically test\, refine\
 , and validate scale data. These methods include Cronbach’s alpha\, explora
 tory factor analysis (EFA)\, confirmatory factor analysis (CFA)\, and basic
  structural equation models testing for predictive validity. Registration a
 nd fee (refundable for students) are required for Zoom link access.
