DESCRIPTION:ReAdOn provides an introductory overview of the full research a
 dministration lifecycle\, from proposal development to award closeout\, and
  incorporates topics in ethics\, compliance and research security. The seri
 es consists of 4 weekly virtual sessions: \n\nWed\, Feb 4\, 11:30am-2:00pm\
 , Session 1: Program Overview and Proposals (note: this session is 30 minut
 es longer) Wed\, Feb 11\, 11:30am-1:30pm\, Session 2: Ethics\, Compliance\,
  and Security in Proposals and Awards Wed\, Feb 18\, 11:30am-1:30pm\, Sessi
 on 3: Award Execution and Post-Award Actions Wed\, Feb 25\, 11:30am-1:30pm\
 , Session 4: Award and Project Management through Closeout  \n\nWhile the s
 eries is especially beneficial for new research administrators\, anyone int
 erested in gaining a deeper understanding of the research administration la
 ndscape at UNC-CH is encouraged to attend. The agenda is available at https
 ://go.unc.edu/ReAdOn-2026-Agenda
