BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes,Lectures
DESCRIPTION:Join EHS Chemical Safety and Biological Safety for Laboratory S
 afety Week Feb. 9 through Feb. 13. This is an annual event dedicated to rec
 ognizing the successes of laboratory health and safety programs while provi
 ding valuable resources to keep our faculty\, staff and students safe.\n\n 
 \n\nAll week long\, EHS will be hosting a series of fun\, interactive train
 ings and workshops. Sign up for workshops that interest you and learn somet
 hing new!\n\n \n\nMaking Safety a Habit: Laboratory Safety Supervisor Works
 hop\n\nThis interactive workshop will help you learn all about safety super
 visor roles and requirements including how to make safety a habit and bring
 ing some fun safety activities back to the lab for a better safety culture.
 \n\n \n\nSharps Safety Workshop\n\nIf you work with needles\, razor blades\
 , or any sharps\, this will be the workshop for you! Partnered with Fisher 
 Scientific. Donuts and coffee will be available.\n\n \n\nAnimal Handling an
 d Occupational Safety\n\nThis great workshop will cover animal handling pre
 sented by Sherie Quillen\, Training Specialist from the Division of Compara
 tive Medicine and the University Employee Occupational Health Clinic.\n\n \
 n\nMental Wellness in the Lab presented by SWELL and a Chemical Compatibili
 ty Workshop\n\nLearn about psychological safety and the importance of welln
 ess and then join us for an interactive session about chemical compatibilit
 y from the Chemical Safety Team.\n\n \n\nIn addition\, we’ll be holding a d
 aily prize giveaway! Starting Feb. 10\, visit go.unc.edu/labsafetyweek26 ea
 ch day for a safety question. Submit your answer for a chance to win. The c
 orrect (or closest) answer will win the prize pin* of the day!\n\n \n\n*Pri
 ze pins are from dOrbital Games
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
