BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performances
DESCRIPTION:FEATURING\n\nThe Abele Saxophone Quartet\n\nSusan Fancher\, sop
 rano saxophone\nRahsaan Barber\, alto saxophone\nHeidi Radtke\, tenor saxop
 hone\nMark Engebretson\, baritone saxophone\n\n \n\nPROGRAM\n\nThe Abele Sa
 xophone Quartet was formed in 2023 by four friends – all music professors (
 at Duke University\, UNC Chapel Hill\, and UNC Greensboro) – for a performa
 nce of worship music in the historic Duke University Chapel. The Abele Saxo
 phone Quartet is named in celebration of the historic accomplishments of Ju
 lian Abele\, primary architect of Duke’s beautiful campus.  The Abele Saxop
 hone Quartet performs an eclectic mix of music from transcriptions of older
  music to original new music and jazz standards arranged for saxophone quar
 tet.  In the Fall of 2025\, the quartet gave a concert of world premieres w
 ritten for the ensemble presented by Duke University’s Music Graduate Stude
 nt Association in conjunction with Duke Music and Erich Barganier.  More re
 cently\, the quartet performed the iconic\, genre-bending work “Super Glue\
 ,” (written by their baritone saxophonist\, Mark Engebretson) at the 2026 N
 avy Band Saxophone Symposium.\n\n \n\nTICKETS\n\n$15 general admission\n$10
  students\, faculty\, and staff\nFree UNC Music students\, faculty\, and st
 aff\n\nPurchase tickets online. Tickets are also available at the door\, 30
  minutes prior to the concert start time.\n\n \n\nPARKING\n\nPlease plan to
  arrive early as parking on campus can be tricky. Learn more about parking 
 and directions to UNC-Chapel Hill’s campus.\n\nThis performance is part of 
 the 2025-2026 William S. Newman Artists series.
DTEND:20260217T013000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260217T003000Z
GEO:35.912607;-79.053261
LOCATION:Hill Hall\, Moeser Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
