DESCRIPTION:The Python Crash Course: Intro to Data introduces fundamental t
 ools for working with tabular data in Python such as Pandas\, Jupyter Noteb
 ooks\, and data visualization packages. We'll work through some applied exa
 mples and survey more specialized packages for data science in Python and t
 alk about next steps on your learning journey.\n\n \n\nThis workshop assume
 s some basic familiarity with Python syntax (for example see “A Whirlwind T
 our of Python”). This workshop will use conda via miniforge\, and Visual St
 udio Code. Setup help will be available before the first session.\n\n \n\nT
 his workshop is offered by University Libraries and will be led by libraria
 ns Philip McDaniel\, Lorin Bruckner\, Michele Hayslett\, Matt Jansen\, and 
