BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes,Lectures
DESCRIPTION:It’s Monday morning and you open your qualitative research proj
 ect folder. Thousands of pages of text\, distributed across 90 in-depth int
 erviews\, await. What’s next? This workshop provides a roadmap for conducti
 ng an applied thematic analysis\, through all major steps in the analytic p
 rocess. Participants will learn the benefits of writing a qualitative data 
 analysis plan\, to ensure that the data collected are analyzed in a way tha
 t best informs the research question(s) and fulfills the study’s objectives
 .\n\nThe instructor will demonstrate how to inductively identify themes\, t
 ransform those themes into codes\, and aggregate codes into an evidence-bas
 ed codebook that is easy to use and that will inform the study’s research q
 uestion(s). Some time will be spent on the topic of integrating codes and i
 nterpreting thematic structure. Basic data reduction techniques will also b
 e presented Hands-on exercises are included for those who wish to practice 
 the concepts learned.\n\nRegistration and fee (refundable for students) are
  required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260220T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260220T150000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Analyzing Qualitative Data for Applied Contexts
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51763475373974
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/analyzing-qualitative-data-for-applied-c
 ontexts-446
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This workshop covers the various stages involved with writing u
 p and publishing findings from a qualitative research study. Course content
  is designed for researchers who intend to publish their findings in a peer
 -reviewed journal\, and well as those who are responsible for reviewing qua
 litative research papers. Topics covered include:\n• Developing a publicati
 on plan\, to ensure smooth workflow\n• Choosing the best journal(s) for you
 r research\n• Drafting concise\, yet informative Abstracts\n• Writing the M
 ethods and Results sections for applied qualitative research papers\n• Post
 -submission: dealing with reviews and editors\nUltimately\, the workshop is
  designed increase participants’ chances of manuscript acceptance. Some tim
 e will\, therefore\, be spent on discussing principles of effective scienti
 fic writing. Course structure includes lecture\, interactive discussion\, a
 nd hands-on exercises. Registration and fee (refundable for students) are r
 equired for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260220T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260220T150000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Writing Up and Publishing Qualitative Research
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50904310621735
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/writing-up-and-publishing-qualitative-re
 search
