BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Spend a Saturday at the Campus Y with fellow Changemakers and g
 et to know our team!\n\nIn this half-day\, summit-style retreat\, we will p
 ause\, connect\, and explore the weaving of personal and communal resilienc
 e—and how this connection can shift the ground in how we approach change. B
 y finding power in the collective\, cultivating compassion for ourselves an
 d others and leaning into community\, we hope students will leave the Summi
 t feeling connected\, grounded\, and inspired to be part of positive\, last
 ing change together.\n\nDuring the Summit\, students will:\n\nJoin others i
 n a community weaving project\,Explore protecting your peace through group 
 dialogue\,Discover practices that support collective mindfulness\,Identify 
 specific ways to move forward together.This CLE credit event includes free 
 snacks\, lunch\, a T-shirt and UNC Y swag. \n\nAll undergraduate and gradua
 te students are welcome.\nRSVP through heel life to reserve your spot!
DTEND:20260221T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260221T143000Z
