BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Performances
DESCRIPTION:“… one nation\, under God\, indivisible\, with liberty and just
 ice for all.”\n\n \n\nIn this compelling and interactive presentation\, sch
 olar and playwright Dr. Sonny Kelly weaves together storytelling\, lecture\
 , poetry\, and dramatic interpretation to confront the painful and persiste
 nt legacies that continue to shape American life.This free public event tak
 es place on Sunday\, February 22\, 2026 from 3:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. at The 
 Friday Center\, 100 Friday Center Dr. in Chapel Hill\; registration is requ
 ired.\n\n \n\nTracing a powerful thread from the colonial era to the presen
 t day\, Dr. Kelly brings to life pivotal figures such as Crispus Attucks\, 
 Frederick Douglass\, and Fred Hampton\, illuminating how their struggles an
 d leadership speak directly to the divisions we face today. With insight an
 d urgency\, he asks the central questions: How did we get where we are\, an
 d what can history teach us about where we go next?\n\n \n\nIndivisible rev
 eals a too-often overlooked American story – one marked not only by oppress
 ion\, but by enduring hope\, resilience\, and the pursuit of unity. This is
  a story that challenges us to listen deeply\, reflect honestly\, and take 
 up the baton from past leaders to help build a more just and indivisible na
 tion.\n\n \n\nMore than a performance\, Indivisible is an experience. Dr. S
 onny Kelly embodies 20 distinct characters\, guiding audiences through unfo
 rgettable stories that span generations. With an exceptional ability to con
 nect\, educate\, and inspire\, Dr. Kelly invites audiences into a safe and 
 courageous space – one that encourages honest engagement with difficult tru
 ths\, exploration of shared humanity\, and the pursuit of healing and unity
 .\n\n\n\n\nIndivisible offers audiences an experience that:\n\nBrings Ameri
 can history vividly to life through interactive theater\, storytelling\, an
 d dramatic interpretation.Illuminates overlooked voices and pivotal figures
  whose legacies shaped…and continue to shape our nation’s story.Encourages 
 reflection and dialogue about unity\, division\, and the meaning of justice
  in America today.Engages both heart and mind\, blending scholarship with p
 owerful live performance.Inspires hope\, resilience\, and connection across
  generations and communities.Creates a welcoming space for thoughtful commu
 nity conversation.Join us for an insightful\, moving\, and inspiring Black 
 History Month experience.\nRegistration is required to attend. Event is fre
 e and open to the public\, and recommended for school grades 3 and up/ages 
 10 and up.\n\n \n\nCampus Life Experience (CLE) credits are available to UN
 C students via https://heellife.unc.edu/
DTEND:20260222T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260222T200000Z
GEO:35.899895;-79.012764
LOCATION:The William and Ida Friday Center at UNC-Chapel Hill
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:"Indivisible" by Sonny Kelly
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51833489464726
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/indivisible-a-one-man-performance-by-dr-
 sonny-kelly
END:VEVENT
