DESCRIPTION:Student Life and Leadership (SLL) centers nonpartisan voter edu
 cation\, empowerment\, and outreach through comprehensive civic engagement 
 initiatives. Student Life and Leadership play an integral role in coordinat
 ing with UNC-Chapel Hill-based stakeholders\, Chapel Hill community partner
 s\, and an expansive population of undergraduate\, graduate\, and professio
 nal students to advance civic engagement.\n\nJoin us for this interactive o
 nline workshop where participants will learn about how social responsibilit
 y translates into collective action\, while providing a foundation for comm
 unity-based impact. In addition to this\, participants will be able to lear
 n how to analyze community issues\, develop skills necessary for finding an
 d advocating community issues that they are passionate about\, practice col
 laborating across diverse perspectives\, and design realistic initiatives t
 hat are grounded in social responsibility and community mobilization. These
  approaches can lead to increased effective\, efficient\, and relevant solu
 tions that are deeply rooted in the needs of the community and its members 
 while driving meaningful change.\n\nPresenters:\n\nTiffany Jones Student Le
 adership Coordinator SLL/THVBethany Daniel Student Leadership Coordinator S
 LL/THVKayla Cooper Student Leadership Coordinator SLL/THV
