DESCRIPTION:Established in 2016\, the UNC School of Nursing (SON) Mobile He
 alth Clinic (MHC) is a nurse-led\, free clinic providing health screenings\
 , patient education\, and referrals to community resources. The clinic is o
 perated by SON faculty\, inter-professional students\, and community volunt
 eers\, addressing gaps in healthcare for vulnerable populations. The MHC ha
 s been awarded the Gold Seal for quality care by the National Association o
 f Free and Charitable Clinics. The upcoming showcase will feature a panel p
 resentation on the clinic’s history\, strategic partnerships\, outreach ini
 tiatives\, and its measurable impact on community health and students’ lear
 ning. The panel discussion will be followed by an optional virtual tour of 
 the clinic and adjacent community resources.\n\nPresenters:\n\nMarianne Coc
 kroft\, PhD\, RN\, Associate Professor Emerita\, UNC SON\, Founding Directo
 r of UNC SON Mobile Health ClinicJean Davison\, DNP\, FNP-BC\, FAAN\, Profe
 ssor\, UNC SON\, Medical Director of UNC SON Mobile Health ClinicAndre Anth
 ony\, CEO\, NeighborUp (Community Partner)Johanne Laboy\, PhD\, Adjunct Ass
 istant Professor\, UNC SONRebecca Hankins\, Director of Development and Com
 munication\, CORA Food PantryCatherine Parrish\, BSN\, Graduate Student
