DESCRIPTION:Tableau is a user-friendly software application used to create 
 static or interactive visualizations and dashboards. Examples can be found 
 on Tableau Public. \n\n \n\nTableau’s drag-and-drop interface provides tool
 s to build a variety of visualizations with no coding required\, and visual
 izations can be embedded in websites by copying and pasting embed code. Att
 endees will get started with Tableau in this hands on workshop by learning 
 how to import data\, create basic charts and maps\, make and publish dashbo
 ards\, and more!\n\n \n\nThis session requires you to have access to Tablea
 u. Please follow the instructions here to download and install Tableau. If 
 you are unable to install the software\, please contact Lorin Bruckner for 
 assistance.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is offered by University Libraries and wi
 ll be led by librarian Lorin Bruckner.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is being offer
 ed remotely via Zoom only. Registrants will receive a Zoom link\; those on 
 the waitlist will not receive a Zoom link unless they are bumped up to a re
 gistered spot. After the workshop\, registrants and those on the waitlist w
 ill receive a link to the workshop recording. You can register on the Unive
 rsity Libraries calendar: https://calendar.lib.unc.edu/event/16021557
