DESCRIPTION:Mental health challenges among underrepresented youth are incre
 asingly prevalent\, often exacerbated by systemic inequities and a lack of 
 culturally responsive support. The Honoring Our Power and Emotions (HOPE Se
 ekers) Program\, developed in collaboration by The Resiliency Collaborative
  (TRC) and UNC Gillings School of Public Health\, is a peer-led initiative 
 designed to empower youth with mental health strategies while fostering lea
 dership and a deep commitment to belonging\, equity\, and inclusion. This s
 ession will explore the ways in which trauma-sensitive practices\, social-e
 motional learning\, and peer-to-peer facilitation models can create safe\, 
 supportive environments for students.\n\nPresenters: \n\nKelsey Lam\, Direc
 tor of Youth Programs\, The Resiliency CollaborativeDr. Caroline Chandler\,
  Assistant Professor\, UNC Gillings School of Public Health: Department of 
 Maternal and Child HealthKirsten Novilla\, Graduate Research Assistant\, UN
 C Gillings School of Public HealthNicolette Rojas\, Graduate Research Assis
 tant\, UNC Gillings School of Public HealthRegister HERE to attend. https:/
 /uncch.givepulse.com/event/821931\n\n \n\nTo view other Carolina Engagement
  Week events\, visit our website.\n\nCarolina Engagement Week is co-hosted 
 by Carolina Across 100\, the Carolina Center for Public Service\, the Carol
 ina Engagement Council\, the Center for Thriving Communities\, NCGrowth\, n
 cIMPACT and UNC Rural.
