DESCRIPTION:Every community holds a secret map of untapped strengths\, incl
 uding local heroes\, quiet spaces\, and hidden resources that\, when connec
 ted\, may be leveraged for significant changes\, even saving lives. Unfortu
 nately\, many people don’t know how to identify and mobilize these assets.\
 n\nIn an immersive\, high-energy session\, learn from participants in CARE4
 Youth\, a collaboration between Carolina Across 100\, the Child and Adolesc
 ent Anxiety and Mood Disorders Program (CHAAMP)\, and ten cross-sector coll
 aborative teams from across North Carolina. During this session\, we will h
 elp you create your own asset map for issues important to you and your comm
 unity\, and share how our focus on existing community strengths through ass
 et mapping is revolutionizing local mental health outcomes.\n\nPresenters:\
 n\nMichael Welker\, Director of Policy and Research Partnerships\, ncIMPACT
  Initiative at the UNC School of GovernmentAbigail Holdsclaw\, Lead Communi
 ty-Based Researcher\, ncIMPACT Initiative at the UNC School of GovernmentLo
 cation: School of Government\, Room 2403\n\nEligible for CLE credit.
