BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:This session explores how meaningful\, lasting partnerships bet
 ween rural communities and campuses are built by centering local voices\, e
 xperiences\, and priorities. This presentation highlights listening not as 
 a passive skill\, but as an active\, intentional practice that fosters trus
 t\, mutual respect\, and shared ownership. Through real-world examples and 
 practical strategies\, participants will learn how campuses and rural commu
 nities can move beyond transactional relationships to co-create solutions t
 hat are culturally grounded\, responsive\, and sustainable. Attendees will 
 leave with actionable insights on engaging communities as equal partners\, 
 strengthening collaboration\, and laying the foundation for impact that tru
 ly begins with listening.\n\n \n\nPresenters: \n\nAerhealle Chace\, Agricul
 ture Department Director\, Freedom Org | Agriculture Education Resource Coo
 rdinator\, Fourtee Acres Resource Market (F.A.R.M)Gail Fallon\, Program Man
 ager\, UNC Rural | Research Project Manager\, UNC School of NursingJada Bro
 oks\, PhD\, MSPH\, RN\, FAAN\, Associate Professor\, UNC School of Nursing 
 \n\nThis event is part of Serving NC Through Rural Community-Campus Partner
 ships\, a conference hosted by UNC Rural as part of Carolina Engagement Wee
 k. To register for this session or for the full conference\, go to: GO.UNC.
 EDU/SERVENC. The conference has both in-person and virtual options.
