CATEGORIES:Meetings and Conferences
DESCRIPTION:The 2021-2022 Dare County Community Health Needs Assessment (CH
 NA) identified mental health as a key factor contributing to mortality rate
 s in the community. The report highlighted suicide as the second leading ca
 use of death among individuals aged 20-34 years. In this session\, presente
 rs share research findings and data that emphasizes the significant role th
 at cultural and contextual factors play in shaping mental health perception
 s and access to care. Future efforts should focus on expanding mental healt
 h resources and support within the community.​\n\n \n\nPresenters: ​\n\nMar
 ie Lina Excellent\, MD\, MPH | UNC Department of Public Health Leadership a
 nd Practice​Sheila F. Davies\, PhD | Deputy County Manager & Department of 
 Health and Human Services Director\, Dare County\, NC​​LaTonia Clark Chalme
 rs\, DNP\, APRN\, PMHNP-BC\, NCBC | UNC School of NursingJudy A. Schmidt\, 
 Ed.D.\, CRC\, LCMHCA | UNC School of Medicine \n\nThis event is part of Ser
 ving NC Through Rural Community-Campus Partnerships\, a conference hosted b
 y UNC Rural as part of Carolina Engagement Week. To register for this sessi
 on or for the full conference\, go to: GO.UNC.EDU/SERVENC. The conference h
 as both in-person and virtual options.
