DESCRIPTION:How can one neighborhood help strengthen an entire community’s 
 food security? This session invites participants into “planting seeds of su
 pport\,” showing how simple\, neighbor-led action can address hunger in Nor
 th Carolina and beyond. Through storytelling\, local data\, and examples fr
 om current PORCH chapters\, attendees will explore how small\, consistent e
 fforts grow into sustained support for local food pantries. The session con
 cludes with an interactive call to action where attendees receive a digital
  toolkit and learn how to share resources in their own hometowns or network
 s to inspire new neighborhood-led solutions. Leave equipped to spark commun
 ity engagement and help plant the next “seed” where it’s needed most.\n\n \
 n\nPresenters:\n\nJordan Cole\, Business Development Coordinator\, PORCH Co
 mmunitiesChristine Cotton\, Founder & CEO\, PORCH
DTEND:20260226T233000Z
