CATEGORIES:Service
DESCRIPTION:Ever looked at your utility bill and thought… what does any of 
 this even mean?\n\nJoin us for an interactive session designed to help resi
 dents better understand the energy information on their utility bills. In t
 his workshop\, we move beyond traditional presentations and engage particip
 ants in creative\, hands-on activities.\n\nThrough guided prompts and small
 -group sketching\, you will explore new ways to visualize and communicate e
 nergy data in ways that are simple and relatable. Our goal is to make utili
 ty bills less confusing and empower residents with knowledge they can use i
 n everyday life. No design or technical experience required\, just curiosit
 y and an interest in understanding your energy use.\n\nPresenters:\n\nRache
 l Oatis\, FT MBA Student\, Kenan-Flagler Business SchoolJoseph James\, Assi
 stant Professor of Sustainable Technology & the Built Environment\, Appalac
 hian State UniversityLocation: Bell Hall 1010\n\n \n\nRegister HERE to atte
 nd. https://uncch.givepulse.com/event/825794\n\n \n\nTo view other Carolina
  Engagement Week events\, visit our website. Carolina Engagement Week is co
 -hosted by Carolina Across 100\, the Carolina Center for Public Service\, t
 he Carolina Engagement Council\, the Center for Thriving Communities\, NCGr
 owth\, ncIMPACT and UNC Rural.
