CATEGORIES:Service
DESCRIPTION:UNC’s Division of OS/OT partnered with Novant Health & UNC Heal
 th’s Ingram Institute’s Novant SERVE initiative to form our program’s first
 -ever Occupational Therapy Rural Health Committee (OTRHC). There are unique
  strengths and opportunities\, as well as barriers and challenges that are 
 imperative to consider when supporting rural healthcare providers and commu
 nities. At the conclusion of this session\, participants will be able to le
 arn about a concentrated effort to broaden OT services and increase workfor
 ce development via the OTRHC program in a 5-county Southeast North Carolina
  region. Participants will be able to reflect on rural community outreach e
 fforts\, and the assets and challenges associated.\n\nPresenters:\n\nSara K
 elleher Peña\, Lead\, Occupational Therapy Rural Health CommitteeDarius Ing
 ram\, Director of Strategic Initiatives\, Novant/UNC partnershipEdye Barbou
 r\, Novant Health SERVE Program Coordinator\, UNC Health Ingram InstituteDr
 . Jennifer Renshaw\, Director of the Occupational Therapy Assistant program
  at Cape Fear Community CollegeMiranda Bravo\, Occupational Therapy student
  class of 2026
