BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Service
DESCRIPTION:As UNC-Chapel Hill faculty\, staff\, and students\, we know the
  incredible work happening here. But most North Carolinians don’t – and the
 y’re rarely thinking about us. How do we bridge that gap to engage communit
 ies effectively?\n\nThis interactive session helps participants step outsid
 e the Chapel Hill bubble to craft messaging that resonates statewide. Using
  the Zietlow Fellowship as an example\, we’ll explore UNC’s role as one par
 tner among many while workshopping clear\, compelling pitches for both comm
 unity audiences and potential funders. You’ll leave with practical tools to
  tell your story authentically\, build trust beyond campus\, and demonstrat
 e impact that matters across North Carolina.\n\nPresenters:\n\nMeridith Whi
 taker\, Foundation Relations Development Officer\, University DevelopmentKy
 lie Seltzer\, Zietlow Postdoctoral Fellow\, Carolina Public Humanities
DTEND:20260227T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
