DESCRIPTION:Panel: The Tactile Page: Poetry\, Process\, and Letterpress\n\n
 Davis Library Room 295\n\nModerator: Pr Carlina Duan\n\nPanelists:\n\nRoss 
 Gay\, 2026 Frank B. Hanes Writer-in-ResidenceNadia Clifton\, Special Collec
 tions Instruction Librarian\, Wilson Special Collections LibraryJosh Hocken
 smith\, Book and print artistAaron Smithers\, Special Collections Research 
 & Instructional Services LibrarianHow do poets pay attention to language as
  a material form? What might the letterpress teach us about rejuvenating ou
 r relationships to making and reading poetic text? How do poets and printer
 s engage with the physical life and process of inking words on a page? Plea
 se join Hanes Writer-in-Residence Ross Gay and the Creative Writing Program
  for a special panel discussion on poetic attention and the letterpress\, w
 here we explore these questions\, and more! This conversation will feature 
 award-winning poet and essayist Ross Gay\, author of Book of Delights and B
 e Holding—alongside UNC librarians\, poets\, and printmakers. Together\, we
  will explore poetry of the handmade\, followed by a live demo of the Unive
 rsity Libraries' letterpress.
