BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This course will be held online only over 3 days. Attendance is
  required as it will not be recorded.\n\nThis 6-hour course provides traini
 ng on how AI can assist a survey project from beginning to the end.\n\nWe w
 ill focus on each step of the research process (Callegaro and Yang\, 2025)\
 n\nPlanningExecutionActivationIn the planning phase there are two sub phase
 s\n1) Ideate and define\n\nAI can be an idea helper and assist on generatin
 g research ideas starting from previously knowledgeA literature review can 
 definitely be assisted by AI and there are specific tools available for tha
 t2) Design and plan\n\nThe design stage is where AI can assist in producing
  design brief\, analysis plan and map the concepts that are going to be mea
 sured using the questionnaireThe execution phase consists of\n3) Data wizar
 d\n\nHere AI has been used to help drafting and pretesting the questionnair
 e\, help writing survey material such as survey invitation and confidential
 ity assurances.4) Analysis copilot\n\nOnce the data collection is under way
 \, AI can assist in automating\, and writing statistical code to analyze th
 e dataset (stat code assistant). It can also be used as  theme discovery\, 
 for coding of open ended answers and data visualization.The activation phas
 e consists of:\n5) Insight partner\n\nHelp summarize findings\, generate re
 ports\, help review the final deliverables such as a research report or a c
 omplete academic paper6) Storytelling aid\n\nDevelop presentation materials
 \, create multi-media artifacts\, generated blog post for different platfor
 ms\, generate images based on content from the researchOrganizational Struc
 ture of the Course \nThe course will be taught in a workshop style where th
 e lectures will be using presentation slides as a roadmap. After each conce
 pt has been introduced and discussed\, the participants will be invited to 
 work on brief hands on exercises with different LLMs such as Gemini\, Claud
 e\, Copilot\, and ChatGPT\n\nParticipants will be strongly encouraged to as
 k questions during lectures\, especially on how the content relates to thei
 r own research.\n\nLearning objectives\nBy the end of the course\, you will
 :\n\nLearn how to prompt LLMs for survey research help and assistanceLearn 
 how to evaluate the quality of LLMs outputsStrengths and challenges of diff
 erent LLMs toolsWhere LLMs are not necessaryEthical usage of LLMs/AI ToolsR
 ecent debate of using LLMs to produce research and write academic papersReg
 istration and fee (refundable for students) are required for Zoom link acce
 ss.
DTEND:20260304T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215834Z
DTSTART:20260304T150000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
