DESCRIPTION:Gen AI tools have the potential to take on tedious tasks and da
 ily drudge work\, freeing us up for the fun parts: thinking\, dreaming\, an
 d doing. In this workshop led by library staff\, learn practical prompting 
 techniques that can turn mile-long to-do lists into actionable plans\, help
 ing you work smarter across all areas of your life.\n\nWe will also crowd-s
 ource tips from attendees on how Gen AI tools have helped them organize tas
 ks for work\, school\, and home life. \n\nAttendees will: \n\nPractice craf
 ting clear prompts to create plans for time management\, prioritizing work 
 or study tasks\, travel\, cleaning\, meal planning\, and more.Understand ho
 w to use AI tools effectively. Share ideas for using Gen AI tools to create
  routines\, manage tasks\, develop study guides\, and save time at work and
  home.This workshop is offered by the University Libraries and will be led 
 by librarian Dayna Durbin and Michelle Hayslett.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is b
 eing offered remotely via Zoom only. You can register through the library c
 alendar. Registrants will receive a Zoom link\; those on the waitlist will 
 not receive a Zoom link unless they are bumped up to a registered spot.
