CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This in-person course introduces learners to the foundations of
  survey development for primary data collection. Students will learn fundam
 ental practices in planning\, designing\, and conducting data collection us
 ing survey research best practices. Core topics will cover:\n• sampling and
  outreach\n• questionnaire development (writing questions\, response option
 s\, and question ordering)\n• visual design considerations of electronic an
 d paper surveys\n• approaches for testing\, and monitoring\nParticipants wi
 ll have the opportunity to draft and review survey questions\, explore reso
 urces for existing survey questions\, and review the strengths and limitati
 ons of various data collection modes. Registration and fee (refundable for 
 students) are required.
DTEND:20260305T170000Z
