BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:LACLI: An Introduction to an International Index for Latin Amer
 ican\, Caribbean\, U.S. Latinx and Iberian Studies with Jesús Alonso Regala
 do (University of Albany\, SUNY)\n\nMarch 5\, 2026 \n\n1:00 - 2:00 p.m.\n\n
 Location: Davis Library\, Room 247 \n\n \n\nJoin project coordinator Jesus 
 Alonso Regalado (University of Albany) for a demonstration of the award-win
 ning international index\, LACLI.   \n\nLaunched by Latin American Northeas
 t Libraries Network (LANE) during the COVID-19 lockdown\, LACLI has become 
 an invaluable research tool for free online resources with full-text conten
 t from Latin America\, the Caribbean\, U.S. Latinos and the Iberian Peninsu
 la. \n\nDuring this session\, you will learn how to use LACLI to find resou
 rces for your coursework and for future teaching and research.  \n\n \n\nLi
 ght refreshments will be served.  \n\n \n\nCo-sponsored by the Institute fo
 r the Study of the Americas and the University Library.
DTEND:20260305T190000Z
