 ive students\, tribal community members and the broader campus community fo
 r a day of traditional dancing\, drumming\, singing\, food and cultural edu
 cation.\n\n \n\nThe powwow serves as both a celebration of Native identity 
 and an opportunity for the university community to learn about and engage w
 ith Indigenous cultures.
