 health-sciences-7498
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Under pressure\, stress pulls leaders out of their roles and in
 to managing mode\, reacting to problems\, controlling tasks\, and just tryi
 ng to get through the day. This session explores what happens in the brain 
 during high-pressure moments and why that makes it harder to lead with clar
 ity. We will look at how pressure pushes leaders toward managing instead of
  leading\, and why that matters for your team’s growth and resilience. Most
  importantly\, you will leave with a simple\, practical tool to help you sl
 ow down\, refocus\, and lead in a way that aligns with your values\, even w
 hen the stakes are high.\n\nWorkshop Objectives:\n\n• Explain how stress im
 pacts the brain and leadership behavior\n• Identify your default leadership
  lane under pressure\n• Shift from managing the crisis to leading through i
 t\n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link and select the “Request” bu
 tton to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260402T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215835Z
DTSTART:20260402T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Leadership in High Pressure Situations 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51561062346500
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/leadership-in-high-pressure-situations
END:VEVENT
