BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Are you considering conducting a systematic review? This sessio
 n offers an overview of the systematic review process\, with an emphasis on
  research methodology. We will focus particularly on pre-review tasks\, lik
 e determining if a review is needed\, developing a research question\, and 
 writing a review protocol. This session is ideal for those who are new to e
 vidence synthesis projects and want to better understand the steps involved
 .\n\n \n\nThis workshop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences Library and l
 ed by Emma Barrett-Catton and Matti Kauftheil.
DTEND:20260413T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215835Z
DTSTART:20260413T150000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Building Better Reviews: Intro to Systematic Review Methods
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52134601413775
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/building-better-reviews-intro-to-systema
 tic-review-methods-7847
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:During this workshop\, participants will be provided useful tip
 s and tools for optimizing the reach of their work. Attendees will gain a s
 eries of strategic skills to help ensure their published research reaches a
  wide audience and its research impact can be tracked.\n\nTopics covered wi
 ll include:\n\nResearch impact measurement optionsOptimizing abstract writi
 ng for database discoverabilityWriting a plain language summary of a studyB
 enefits of ORCID and how to set up an ORCIDUnderstanding open access publis
 hing and author rightsThis workshop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences L
 ibrary and led by Emma Barrett-Catton
DTEND:20260414T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215835Z
DTSTART:20260414T150000Z
LOCATION:
