URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/breathing-techniques-to-relieve-stress-a
 nd-improve-health-6116
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Financial goals are the specific long- and short-term objective
 s to be attained through financial planning and management efforts. Among p
 ersonal financial goals are things such as 1) financial security 2) travel 
 3) education planning 4) retirement planning and 5) estate planning. Being 
 able to succeed in reaching these goals requires a structure and plan with 
 appropriate milestones\, along with the ability to make adjustments along t
 he way.\n\n \n\nWorkshop Objectives\nAt the end of this workshop\, you will
  be able to:\n• Understand the importance of having realistic financial goa
 ls clearly defined\n• Recognize the importance of managing your finances to
  address these goals\n• Develop achievable steps to stay on track\n• Take a
 ppropriate action to monitor progress toward the goals and make adjustments
  as needed.\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link and select t
 he “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260529T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215836Z
DTSTART:20260529T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Financial Planning for Life
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375548073882
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/financial-planning-for-life
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Certain individuals appear to succeed against all odds. Despite
  severe hardships such as living through war\, witnessing the death of a lo
 ved one\, having a chronic illness\, being a victim of abuse or dealing wit
 h unemployment\, certain people not only adapt but actually thrive. These p
 eople possess a quality known as “resilience.” This workshop will examine t
 he characteristics of resilience and discover ways to introduce greater res
 ilience into our lives.\n\n \n\nWorkshop Objectives\nAt the end of this wor
 kshop\, you will be able to:\nDescribe what resilience really is\n• Describ
 e the concept of resilience as it relates to children and adults\n• Describ
 e the characteristics of resilient people\n• Describe how emotional control
 \, self-awareness and strong relationships relate to resiliency\nIdentify y
 our own resilient capacities\n• Identify you unique resilient strengths and
  areas for development\n• Recognize which situations are most stressful\nDe
 scribe resilience building strategies\n• Describe techniques to enhance res
 ilience through changing your perception\, taking decisive action and engag
 ing in appropriate self-care.\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration
  link and select the “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260603T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215836Z
DTSTART:20260603T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Resiliency: Bouncing Back After a Setback
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375565550491
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/resiliency-bouncing-back-after-a-setback
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:For a long time\, the scientific community believed we were bor
 n with a certain number of brain cells and neural pathways and that\, once 
 damaged\, they could not be repaired. In reality\, our brains are much more
  flexible. Depending on our lifestyle\, we can weaken or destroy connection
 s\, or create new\, stronger ones. Engaging regularly in certain behaviors 
 and activities\, like physical exercise\, addressing mental health issues\,
  meditation\, and learning a new language or musical instrument\, support n
 ew wiring and can make existing pathways stronger. Essentially\, we can slo
 w down or somewhat prevent cognitive decline by doing challenging mental ex
 ercises to keep our brains fit for optimal power.\n\n \n\nWorkshop Objectiv
 es\nAt the end of this workshop\, you will be able to:\nIdentify traits of 
 a healthy brain:\n• The ability to learn new skills\n• Judgment and intuiti
 on\n• Memory and perception\nIdentify barriers to good brain health:\n• Dep
 ression\n• Chronic stress\n• Unhealthy lifestyle\nIdentify methods for opti
 mal cognitive health:\n• Engaging in new skills and mentally challenging ac
 tivities\n• Meditation\n• Physical exercise\n• Brain training\n\n \n\nClick
  on Carolina Talent registration link and select the “Request” button to au
 tomatically enroll.
DTEND:20260610T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215836Z
DTSTART:20260610T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Mental Fitness for Optimal Brain Power
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375586889526
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/mental-fitness-for-optimal-brain-power-7
 0
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Your body responds to the way you think\, feel and act. This is
  often called the “mind/body connection.” When you are stressed\, anxious o
 r upset\, your body tries to tell you that something isn’t right. For examp
 le\, high blood pressure might develop after a particularly stressful event
 \, such as the death of a loved one. People with good emotional health are 
 aware of their thoughts\, feelings and behaviors. They have learned healthy
  ways to cope with the stress and problems that are a normal part of life. 
 They feel good about themselves and have healthy relationships. Poor emotio
 nal health can weaken your body’s immune system\, making you more likely to
  get colds and other infections during emotionally difficult times. Also\, 
 when you are feeling stressed\, anxious or upset\, you may not take care of
  your health as well as you should. You may not feel like exercising\, eati
 ng nutritious foods or taking medicine that your doctor prescribes. Abuse o
 f alcohol\, tobacco or other drugs may also be a sign of poor emotional hea
 lth.\n\n \n\nWorkshop Objectives\nAt the end of this workshop\, you will be
  able to:\nIdentify the relationship between mind and body\n• Describe how 
 the body influences emotional and mental functioning\n• Describe how our em
 otions\, beliefs and self talk impact our body\n• Identify symptoms of a po
 ssible mind/body disconnection\nIdentify ways to enhance the mind/body conn
 ection\n• Describe methods for achieving balance in life\n• Identify ways t
 o express feelings appropriately\n• Describe the importance of taking care 
 of your health\n• Describe ways to enhance awareness\nIdentify your persona
 l action plan for mind/body connection\n• Recognize the importance of consu
 lting with your physician\n• Describe which mind/body tools need to develop
 \n• List outside resources for further help\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talen
 t registration link and select the “Request” button to automatically enroll
 .
DTEND:20260617T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215836Z
DTSTART:20260617T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Connecting Mind and Body for Healthy Living
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375603971825
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/connecting-mind-and-body-for-healthy-liv
 ing
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Organizations are investing in benefits to improve employee wel
 lbeing\, and taking on initiatives to foster a culture of wellbeing in the 
 workplace. However\, many employees still feel that their job is an obstacl
 e to their wellbeing rather than a help. What can you do as a manager to sh
 ift that perception? This session will discuss practical ways to show emplo
 yees that you and your organization support their wellbeing.\n\n \n\nWorksh
 op Objectives\nThis training will help you:\n• Describe ways in which a man
 ager can promote employee wellbeing\n• Become an advocate for wellbeing res
 ources available to your employees\n• Have productive conversations with em
 ployees to address concerns that work is negatively impacting their wellbei
 ng\n• Lead by example in demonstrating that you place a high priority on yo
 ur own wellbeing\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link and sel
 ect the “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260624T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260306T215836Z
DTSTART:20260624T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Supporting Employee Well-Being: What can you do as a manager?
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51375618272748
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/supporting-employee-well-being-what-can-
 you-do-as-a-manager-1734
